---
By: David Mamet
Locus:
  Page: 383
  Verse: 17
Tags:
  - Problems
---
The problems of the world, AIDS, cancer, nuclear war, pollution, are,
finally, no more soluble than the problem of a tree which has borne fruit：
the apples are overripe and they are falling—what can be done? Nothing can
be done, and nothing needs to be done.
